om%3Fh%3D31b7d83476a9ef2aab1e86b1724114c32553f8f3c248bb0b7887e2e1861d7eb2%26postID%3D6661aa38e01a10ede1c06e83%26postSlug%3Dreddit-cofounder-top-4-tips-startup-success-alexis-ohanian-masterclass-2024-6%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.masterclass.com%252Fclasses%252Falexis-ohanian-teaches-building-your-startup%252Fchapters%252Ffailing-and-pivoting%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2023%20episode%20of%20MasterClass%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Ohanian%20explained%20what%20it's%20like%20to%20be%20on%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20investment%20table%20and%20shared%20his%20top%20tips%20for%20startup%20founders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEntrepreneurship%20is%20as%20simple%20as%20having%20ideas%20and%20doing%20them%2C%20and%20everyone%20is%20capable%20of%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20it%20had%20never%20been%20easier%20to%20become%20an%20entrepreneur.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20founder%20today%20has%20more%20and%20more%20leverage%20than%20they%20did%20a%20decade%20ago.%20So%20many%20of%20the%20different%20components%20have%20been%20automated%20or%20semi-automated%20through%20software.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20successful%20means%20being%20able%20to%20turn%20these%20ideas%20into%20a%20workable%20product%2C%20and%20having%20the%20resistance%20to%20keep%20going%2C%20Ohanian%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b48720eb-5cad-4375-8011-c297d2c64289%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Be%20a%20generalist%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20being%20a%20successful%20start-up%20founder%20is%20being%20relentless%20and%20adaptable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEarly%20on%2C%20you%20have%20to%20be%20willing%20to%20wear%20all%20the%20hats%20%E2%80%94%20you%20have%20to%20be%20willing%20to%20be%20a%20generalist%2C%26quot%3B%20Ohanian%20said%20during%20the%20class.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeaders%20need%20to%20be%20willing%20to%20take%20on%20jobs%20outside%20their%20comfort%20zone%2C%20even%20if%20they're%20not%20used%20to%20doing%20them.%20According%20to%20Ohanian%2C%20this%20attitude%20also%20needs%20to%20extend%20to%20early%20employees%20at%20start-ups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20scrappiness%20needs%20to%20infect%20not%20just%20the%20founding%20team%20but%20those%20early%20employees%20because%20you're%20going%20to%20find%20yourself%20in%20a%20situation%20where%20something%20just%20needs%20to%20get%20done%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2297a759c7-68ba-4fd5-aac3-3a25d8cd3564%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Ship%20something%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20it's%20basic%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20important%20to%20show%20investors%20that%20your%20ideas%20can%20work%20in%20the%20real%20world%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20it's%20a%20basic%20prototype.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMinimum%20viable%20product%26quot%3B%20(MVP)%20is%20a%20term%20used%20in%20the%20start-up%20world%20to%20describe%20a%20product%20with%20enough%20features%20to%20attract%20early%20adopter%20customers%20and%20validate%20a%20product%20idea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20something%20you%20can%20put%20in%20front%20of%20customers%2C%20or%20users%2C%20or%20potential%20clients%2C%20or%20partners.%20It's%20gives%20you%20some%20idea%20of%20whether%20or%20not%20your%20on%20the%20right%20track%2C%26quot%3B%20Ohanian%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20may%20be%20enough%20to%20draw%20in%20some%20investors%2C%20but%20building%20this%20foundation%20also%20means%20startups%20have%20something%20to%20work%20on%20and%20improve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BExecution%20is%20everything%2C%26quot%3B%20Ohanian%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20not%20just%20doing%20the%20work%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20doing%20the%20right%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFiguring%20out%20your%20edge%20and%20continuously%20improving%20the%20product%20%26quot%3Bis%20the%20most%20important%20thing%20you%20could%20spend%20your%20time%20on%20in%20those%20first%20six%20months%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2264c75dc9-5df2-4ab9-90c0-dc9aa07cfcde%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Get%20comfortable%20hearing%20no%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESecuring%20funding%20can%20be%20a%20lengthy%20process%20for%20start-ups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20told%20no%20repeatedly%20is%20just%20a%20%26quot%3Bpart%20of%20fundraising%2C%26quot%3B%20Ohanian%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20not%20a%20single%20CEO%20out%20there%20who%20has%20not%20been%20told%20no%20more%20times%20than%20yes%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BThe%20nature%20of%20being%20an%20entrepreneur%20is%20getting%20really%20comfortable%20hearing%20no.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOhanian%20suggested%20that%20early%20founders%20focus%20on%20shipping%20something%2C%20even%20if%20it's%20basic%2C%20and%20sharing%20that%20widely%20on%20social%20media.%20Gaining%20a%20social%20profile%20could%20encourage%20investors%20to%20come%20directly%20to%20founders%2C%20allowing%20them%20to%20do%20less%20cold-calling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220a6cbdfa-6f47-4c01-9c29-5d5ebf890837%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Build%20the%20right%20team%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHiring%20the%20first%20employee%20is%20a%20major%20milestone%20for%20any%20startup%2C%20but%20it's%20also%20a%20decision%20that%20could%20make%20or%20break%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHiring%20well%2C%20hiring%20quickly%20is%20very%20hard%20to%20do%3B%20there's%20no%20hack%2C%26quot%3B%20Ohanian%20said%2C%20noting%20that%20the%20rise%20of%20remote%20work%20had%20made%20the%20process%20even%20more%20complicated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20first%2010%20employees%20you%20hire%20are%20going%20to%20define%20the%20culture%20for%20the%20company%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20time.%20An%20ideal%20hire%20needs%20to%20be%20willing%20to%20help%20build%20the%20plane%20while%20you're%20flying%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOhanian%20recommended%20founders%20look%20outside%20their%20network%20when%20hiring%20and%20aggressively%20reach%20out%20to%20talent%20on%20platforms%20like%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20suggests%20founders%20focus%20on%20creating%20job%20ads%20that%20stand%20out%3A%20%26quot%3BIn%20an%20environment%20where%20everyone%20is%20doing%20something%20the%20same%20way%2C%20being%20demonstrably%20different%2C%20it%20gives%20people%20something%20to%20want%20to%20talk%20about.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-cofounder-top-4-tips-startup-success-alexis-ohanian-masterclass-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717756769000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6661d666cc442a2f676e96a9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-cofounder-top-4-tips-startup-success-alexis-ohanian-masterclass-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Alexis%20Ohanian%20gives%20founders%20some%20tips%20for%20turning%20their%20ideas%20into%20successful%20businesses%20in%20an%20episode%20of%20MasterClass%20from%202023.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bnolan%40insider.com%20(Beatrice%20Nolan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-cofounder-top-4-tips-startup-success-alexis-ohanian-masterclass-2024-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Sensex%20up%201%2C600%20pts%2C%20Nifty%20near%2023%2C300%3A%20Why%20markets%20surged%20after%20RBI%20policy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717756741000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2019-03%2F08%2Fthumb%2Ffeaturecrop%2F400X400%2F1551991482-3959.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fsensex-up-1-462-pts-nifty-tops-23-200-why-markets-surged-after-rbi-policy-124060700402_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Stock%20market%20updates%2C%20June%207%3A%20The%20stock%20market%20rally%20was%20fuelled%20by%20gains%20in%