C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMichael%20Doolin%20has%20worked%20in%20HR%20for%2036%20years.%20He%20was%20an%20HR%20direct%20for%20PwC%2C%20British%20Airways%20and%20DPD.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20said%20employees%20often%20don't%20get%20the%20recognition%20or%20feedback%20they%20want%20from%20their%20bosses.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20HR%20veteran%20shares%20what%20signs%20employees%20can%20look%20for%20that%20suggest%20they%20are%20good%20at%20their%20jobs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20transcribed%20conversation%20with%20Michael%20Doolin%2C%20a%20former%20HR%20director%20at%20PwC%2C%20British%20Airways%20and%20DPD%20based%20in%20Ireland.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%2036%20years%20in%20HR%2C%20you%20realize%20a%20few%20things%20about%20people.%20I%20think%2050%25%20of%20the%20workforce%20come%20to%20do%20a%20good%20job%20and%20simply%20want%20a%20%26quot%3BThank%20you%26quot%3B%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day.%20Too%20many%20employers%20fail%20to%20recognize%20that%20simple%20acknowledgment%20can%20go%20a%20long%20way%20in%20keeping%20people%20engaged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20don't%20always%20know%20where%20they%20stand%20at%20work%20regarding%20performance.%20Ambitious%20people%20focused%20on%20advancement%20will%20be%20looking%20for%20recognition%20daily.%20Subtle%20hints%2C%20like%20a%20boss%20inviting%20someone%20to%20lunch%20or%20spending%20more%20time%20with%20someone%20else%2C%20might%20generate%20a%20sense%20of%20inequality%2C%20which%2C%20at%20its%20extreme%2C%20can%20magnify%20feelings%20of%20stress%2C%20anxiety%2C%20and%20insecurity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerformance%20management%2C%20like%20appraisals%2C%20should%20be%20done%20more%20regularly%20than%20once%20a%20year.%20It%20should%20be%20an%20ongoing%20debate%20between%20you%20and%20your%20boss.%20There's%20a%20great%20mantra%20from%20a%20previous%20boss%20of%20mine%3A%20there%20should%20be%20no%20surprises.%20To%20ensure%20that%2C%20employers%20should%20have%20discussions%20and%20performance%20reviews%20throughout%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20me%2C%20being%20good%20at%20your%20job%20is%20about%20how%20much%20you're%20growing%2C%20how%20much%20you're%20adding%20value%2C%20and%20how%20much%20you're%20recognized.%20If%20your%20boss%20isn't%20vocal%20about%20your%20performance%2C%20these%20are%20signs%20you're%20still%20performing%20well%20at%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fe685ecd-e58a-4cb7-bd13-ac0934e8f5cb%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWorking%20efficiently%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ease%20at%20which%20you%20can%20do%20your%20job%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0how%20challenging%20or%20awkward%20it%20might%20be%20%E2%80%94%20is%20a%20good%20indication%20of%20how%20you're%20performing.%20You%20might%20find%20that%20your%20emails%20are%20going%20down%20or%20you've%20got%20time%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20week%2C%20or%20month%20because%20you've%20overachieved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConversely%2C%20if%20you%20keep%20more%20paper%20in%20the%20bottom%20left-hand%20drawer%20because%20you%20haven't%20gotten%20to%20it%2C%20it%20may%20signal%20that%20you're%20underperforming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20being%20said%2C%20having%20a%20never-ending%20inbox%20doesn't%20mean%20you're%20doing%20badly.%20Automate%20as%20much%20as%20possible%20and%20embrace%20technology%20and%20better%20practices.%20These%20are%20all%20signs%20of%20a%20proactive%20learner.%20Set%20up%20email%20rules%20so%20that%20you%20only%20see%20the%20things%20that%20are%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228379ca9c-145f-4a2a-a530-ee470fb7ca50%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EProper%20planning%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPlanning%20and%20prioritizing%20work%20is%20a%20sign%20that%20you're%20working%20well.%20Your%20boss%20shouldn't%20be%20getting%20any%20surprises.%20Leaving%20things%20to%20the%20last%20minute%20and%20giving%20rushed%20responses%20does%20not%20convey%20competency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20might%20be%20giving%20frequent%20reports%20and%20updates%2C%20and%20you'll%20be%20showing%20up%20to%20work%20on%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b426f8e4-45cb-40af-83ab-72c54c1563c8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EPositive%20feedback%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20getting%20positive%20comments%20from%20colleagues%2C%20clients%2C%20and%20customers%20on%20work-related%20matters%2C%20it's%20a%20sign%20that%20you're%20doing%20something%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f5dc6581-8fe7-4072-b23c-561a8cef6059%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EEngagement%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20greatest%20indications%20of%20performance%20is%20how%20engaged%20you%20are%20at%20work%2C%20informally%20and%20formally.%20Engagement%20can%20be%20evidenced%20in%20a%20number%20of%20ways%3A%20attendance%2C%20appearance%2C%20collaboration%20with%20colleagues%2C%20emails%20going%20up%20or%20down%2C%20and%20general%20intellectual%20curiosity%20or%20participation%20in%20workplace%20meetings%2C%20gatherings%2C%20or%20conversations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20an%20employer%2C%20getting%20to%20know%20your%20people%20and%20how%20they%20operate%20is%20crucial.%20It's%20underrated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20operate%20differently%20when%20they're%20under%20pressure.%20Employers%20can%20identify%20those%20stress%20points%20if%20they%20have%20a%20better%20sense%20of%20that%20person's%20motivations%20and%20moods.%20The%20best%20way%20to%20do%20this%20is%20by%20spending%20time%20with%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20work%20environment%20should%20not%20focus%20solely%20on%20the%20workplace.%20We%20need%20to%20remember%20that%20the%20individual%20is%20someone%20who%20brings%20unique%20talents.%20Therefore%2C%20seeing%20the%20person%20as%20a%20whole%20rather%20than%20only%20what%20they%20bring%20to%20their%20daily%20tasks%20is%20important%20%E2%80%94%20both%20for%20the%20employer%20and%20the%20employee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%