s%20raising%20eyebrows%20among%20privacy%20advocates%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222317%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Meta's%20Instagram%2C%20Facebook%2C%20and%20WhatsApp%20apps%20displayed%20on%20a%20smartphone.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66621023d0b8e1c832ccbfe0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMeta%20wants%20to%20use%20old%20Facebook%20data%20to%20train%20its%20AI%20models.%3Cp%3Epicture%20alliance%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20European%20advocacy%20group%20filed%20complaints%20in%2011%20countries%20over%20a%20new%20Meta%20AI%20policy.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENOYB%2C%20or%20None%20of%20Your%20Business%2C%20said%20Meta's%20new%20policy%20would%20let%20it%20scrape%20user%20data%20to%20train%20AI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EUnlike%20American%20users%2C%20Europeans%20have%20an%20option%20to%20opt%20out%20of%20sharing%20their%20information.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20is%20scrambling%20to%20compete%20in%20the%20red-hot%20AI%20arms%20race%2C%20but%20an%20advocacy%20group%20is%20demanding%20nearly%20a%20dozen%20European%20countries%20force%20Meta%20to%20pump%20the%20breaks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20European%20advocacy%20group%20announced%20complaints%20in%2011%20European%20countries%20over%20an%20upcoming%20Meta%20policy%20change%20that%20would%20allow%20it%20to%20scrape%20old%20user%20data%20from%20Facebook%20to%20train%20its%20artificial%20intelligence%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20%26quot%3Bplans%20to%20use%20years%20of%20personal%20posts%2C%20private%20images%2C%20or%20online%20tracking%20data%20for%20an%20undefined%20'AI%20technology'%20that%20can%20ingest%20personal%20data%20from%20any%20source%20and%20share%20any%20information%20with%20undefined%20'third%20parties%2C'%26quot%3B%20the%20group%2C%20aptly%20named%20None%20of%20Your%20Business%2C%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnoyb.eu%2Fen%2Fnoyb-urges-11-dpas-immediately-stop-metas-abuse-personal-data-ai%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENOYB%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20in%20a%20press%20announcement%20asking%20authorities%20to%20step%20in%20and%20suspend%20the%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta's%20updated%20privacy%20policy%20is%20scheduled%20to%20go%20live%20in%20late%20June.%20It%20would%20impact%20some%20400%20million%20European%20users%2C%20NOYB%20said.%20The%20group%20said%20it%20was%20concerning%20that%20users%20would%20have%20to%20manually%20opt%20out%20of%20providing%20data%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInstead%20of%20asking%20users%20for%20their%20consent%20(opt-in)%2C%20Meta%20argues%20that%20it%20has%20a%20legitimate%20interest%20that%20overrides%20the%20fundamental%20right%20to%20data%20protection%20and%20privacy%20of%20European%20users%2C%26quot%3B%20NOYB%20said.%20Europe%20has%20strict%20data%20privacy%20laws%20outlined%20in%20the%20European%20Union's%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgdpr-compliance-checklist-2018-05%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EGeneral%20Data%20Protection%20Regulation%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20went%20into%20effect%20in%202018%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eand%20has%20had%20a%20profound%20effect%20on%20Big%20Tech's%20operations%20in%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENOYB%20filed%20complaints%20in%20Austria%2C%20Belgium%2C%20France%2C%20Germany%2C%20Greece%2C%20Italy%2C%20Ireland%2C%20the%20Netherlands%2C%20Norway%2C%20Poland%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-election-tool-voter-privacy-user-data-collection-european-union-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESpain%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Meta%20spokesperson%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider%2C%20but%20the%20company%20previously%20told%20Reuters%20that%20its%20new%20policy%20followed%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20confident%20that%20our%20approach%20complies%20with%20privacy%20laws%2C%20and%20our%20approach%20is%20consistent%20with%20how%20other%20tech%20companies%20are%20developing%20and%20improving%20their%20AI%20experiences%20in%20Europe%20(including%20Google%20and%20Open%20AI)%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Meta%20spokesperson%20said%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Ftechnology%2Fmeta-gets-11-eu-complaints-over-use-personal-data-train-ai-models-2024-06-06%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReuters%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20United%20States%2C%20Meta%20AI%20has%20already%20had%20access%20to%20public%20user%20data%20and%20private%20chat%20conversations%20on%20Facebook%2C%20Instagram%2C%20and%20WhatsApp%2C%20and%20there%20is%20no%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eway%20to%20fully%20opt%20out%20of%20sharing%20your%20information%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Ftechnology%2F2024%2F05%2F31%2Fopt-out-ai-training-meta-chatgpt%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-privacy-policy-change-concerns-scrape-facebook-data-train-ai-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717755061000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66621597d0b8e1c832ccc3cd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-privacy-policy-change-concerns-scrape-facebook-data-train-ai-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Meta%20is%20about%20to%20start%20scraping%20old%20Facebook%20data%20to%20train%20its%20AI%20models%2C%20alarming%20advocacy%20groups%20in%20Europe.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kbalevic%40businessinsider.com%20(Katie%20Balevic)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-privacy-policy-change-concerns-scrape-facebook-data-train-ai-