0and%20disappointing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20will%20be%20exciting%20because%20you'll%20need%20to%20build%20large%20systems%20at%20scale%2C%20but%20before%20you%20can%20write%20any%20code%2C%20you%20must%20understand%20the%20organization's%20business%20context%20and%20its%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20need%20to%20partner%20very%20closely%20with%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbreak-into-tech-product-manager-skills-experience-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20product%20managers%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20business%20analysts.%20Sometimes%2C%20you%20must%20partner%20with%20many%20to%20understand%20all%20business%20units.%20Even%20if%20the%20company%20has%20multiple%20units%2C%20the%20data%20system%20you%20build%20should%20serve%20all%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20writing%20a%20line%20of%20code%2C%20you%20must%20figure%20out%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EWhat%20data%20needs%20to%20be%20collected%3F%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHow%20is%20the%20organization%20planning%20to%20use%20the%20data%3F%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHow%20fresh%20should%20the%20data%20be%3F%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20these%20questions%20have%20technical%2C%20architectural%2C%20and%20efficiency%20implications.%20A%20good%20data%20engineer%20delivers%20the%20best%20system%20that%20balances%20the%20organization's%20needs%2C%20costs%2C%20and%20timelines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20data%20engineers%20consider%20future%20needs%20and%20designs%20with%20them%20in%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d4b3ed86-0efe-4075-ad8c-d92d2bf60926%5C%22%3E2.%20It's%20a%20fast-paced%20job%20that%20continuously%20evolves%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20don't%20like%20to%20be%20challenged%20constantly%2C%20then%20data%20engineering%20may%20not%20be%20for%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20engineering%20is%20a%20field%20that%20evolves%20very%20fast%2C%20and%20you%20need%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20it.%20Data%20is%20growing%20exponentially%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-workers-employees-dissatisfied-jobs-new-data-labor-market-glassdoor-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20systems%20and%20techniques%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20needed%20to%20manage%20vast%20amounts%20of%20data.%20Yesterday's%20systems%20are%20obsolete%2C%20and%20this%20may%20seem%20overwhelming%20due%20to%20the%20speed%20of%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20happened%20to%20me%20in%20the%20early%20stages%20of%20my%20career.%20There%20was%20so%20much%20to%20learn%20and%20so%20little%20time.%20I%20was%20working%20at%20a%20startup%20and%20had%20to%20hit%20the%20ground%20running.%20Early%20on%2C%20I%20read%20and%20learned%20at%20night%20and%20developed%20during%20the%20day.%20This%20helped%20me%20get%20a%20better%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecruiter-how-filter-applications-software-engineering-job-post-atl-interview-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunderstanding%20of%20software%20engineering%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20my%20peers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20I%20set%20aside%20a%20couple%20of%20hours%20a%20week%20to%20browse%20and%20read%20about%20the%20latest%20developments%20in%20my%20field.%20I%20know%20I%20don't%20cover%20everything%2C%20but%20I%20try%20to%20stay%20updated%20as%20much%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-is-paying-off-for-some-major-cloud-providers-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrends%20in%20the%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20space%20have%20brought%20Generative%20AI%20and%20technologies%20like%20Vector%20Databases%20and%20Retrieval-Augmented%20Generation%20techniques.%20These%20unlock%20new%20possibilities%20but%20also%20bring%20new%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20everything%2C%20but%20this%20shouldn't%20make%20you%20give%20up.%20Register%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-best-tech-newsletters-emails-2017-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank