mit%5Bing%5D%20the%20inclusion%20of%20satire%20and%20humor%20content%26quot%3B%20in%20answers%2C%20and%20simply%20not%20using%20AI%20answers%20in%20some%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20another%20argument%20in%20favor%20of%20%26quot%3Bthere's%20less%20to%20see%26quot%3B%20comes%20from%20BrightEdge%2C%20a%20search%20optimization%20company.%20BrightEdge%20says%20it%20has%20been%20tracking%20Google's%20AI%20Overviews%20since%20Google%20first%20started%20testing%20them%20last%20fall%2C%20initially%20with%20people%20who%20signed%20up%20to%20try%20them%20out%20via%20its%20experimental%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flabs.google%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%20Labs%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20one%20point%2C%20says%20BrightEdge%20founder%20Jim%20Yu%2C%20some%20keywords%20were%20generating%20AI%20answers%2084%25%20of%20the%20time.%20But%20by%20the%20time%20of%20Google%20I%2FO%2C%20when%20the%20company%20announced%20that%20AI%20answers%20were%20going%20to%20roll%20out%20to%20most%20users%2C%20that%20number%20had%20dropped%20to%20around%2030%25.%20And%20within%20a%20week%20of%20the%20announcement%2C%20that%20number%20had%20dropped%20again%20%E2%80%94%20this%20time%20to%20around%2011%25.%20(Google%20PR%20says%20it%20takes%20issue%20with%20BrightEdge's%20methodology%2C%20and%20says%20its%20results%20are%20inaccurate%3B%20Google%20didn't%20offer%20its%20own%20statistics.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22chart%20of%20AI%20results%20on%20Google%20search%20result%20pages%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66621bc4d0b8e1c832ccc7ae%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBrightEdge%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20which%20is%20conclusive!%20But%20it%20does%20look%2C%20for%20now%2C%20like%20Google%20might%20have%20weathered%20the%20worst%20of%20a%20storm%20it%20created%20for%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%2