%2C200%20apple%20trees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresently%2C%20his%20farm%20now%20has%20700%20kiwi%20plants%20yielding%209%20tonnes%20of%20fruit%20annually%2C%20with%20expected%20production%20increases.%20He%20also%20developed%20two%20nurseries%20with%2012%2C000%20saplings%20for%20additional%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2FKiwi-farm1-1647262025.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Swaastik%20farms'%20organic%20kiwi.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2FKiwi-farm1-1647262025.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2FKiwi-farm1-1647262025-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2FKiwi-farm1-1647262025-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2FKiwi-farm1-1647262025-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2FKiwi-farm1-1647262025-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-279013%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EKiwis%20at%20Mandeep%E2%80%99s%20farm.%20Picture%20credit%3A%20Mandeep%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E7.%20Rohan%20Prakash%E2%80%99s%20certified%20mangoes%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGrowing%20up%20in%20a%20farming%20family%20watching%20his%20father%20and%20grandfather%2C%20Rohan%20Prakash%20felt%20an%20affinity%20for%20fields%20and%20farms.%20The%20engineer%E2%80%99s%20passion%20for%20agriculture%20led%20him%20to%20convert%20their%20farm%20into%20a%20completely%20organic%20operation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20shift%20to%20organic%20farming%20yielded%20immediate%20improvements%20in%20the%20quality%20and%20size%20of%20their%20mangoes.%20The%20transformation%20process%20started%20during%20his%20second%20year%20of%20college%20when%20he%20and%20his%20father%20decided%20to%20replace%20pesticides%20with%20Neem%20oil%20extract.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEncouraged%20by%20the%20results%2C%20Rohan%20branded%20their%20produce%20as%20%E2%80%9CSure%20Organics%E2%80%9D.%20Rohan%E2%80%99s%20farm%20grows%20various%20mango%20varieties%2C%20including%20%3Cem%3Edasheri%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Elangra%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Echaunsa%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3Esafeda%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20along%20with%20lychee%20and%20turmeric.%20Over%20three%20years%2C%20his%20farm%20achieved%20organic%20certification%2C%20boosting%20their%20revenue%20significantly%20and%20increasing%20overall%20productivity%20by%2040%25.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E8.%20S%20Sivaganesh%E2%80%99s%20homecoming%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWorking%20as%20an%20engineer%20at%20an%20atomic%20station%20in%20Rajasthan%2C%20S%20Sivaganesh%20always%20felt%20something%20was%20amiss.%20Growing%20up%20in%20nature%20with%20a%20farmer%20father%2C%20he%20longed%20to%20go%20back%20home%20and%20start%20farming.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20working%20for%20four%20years%2C%20he%20decided%20to%20move%20back%20to%20his%20hometown%20in%20Meenakshipuram%2C%20at%20the%20Kerala-Tamil%20Nadu%20border%2C%20in%202010.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESivaganesh%20asked%20his%20father%20for%206%20acres%20of%20land%20to%20practise%20organic%20farming.%20%E2%80%9CI%20planted%20nutmegs%20as%20an%20intercrop%20along%20the%20coconut%20plantations%20of%201%2C600%2C%20and%20took%20up%20mango%2C%20turmeric%2C%20pepper%2C%20and%20areca%20nut%20plantations%20across%20my%206-acre%20farm%20along%20with%20it.%20I%20used%20organic%20methods%20for%20all%20the%20crops%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20started%20meaning%20Rs%202%20lakh%20per%20acre%20as%20a%20combined%20income%20from%20all%20plantations.%20His%20secret%20%E2%80%94%20farming%20techniques%20such%20as%20the%20intercropping%20method%2C%20a%20practice%20of%20growing%20multiple%20crops%20in%20close%20proximity%2C%20and%20the%20drip-irrigation%20technique%2C%20among%20other%20agriculture-allied%20practices.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Edited%20by%20Padmashree%20Pande)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716983032000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2FRoja-Reddy-owner-of-Nisarga-Native-Farms-1663076088-1-1683120242.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D351436%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Does%20leaving%20your%209%20to%205%20job%20and%20moving%20to%20organic%20farming%20sound%20interesting%3F%20These%20stories%20will%20leave%20you%20motivated.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Tina%20Freese%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F351436%2Fhow-to-start-organic-farming-techies-switching-to-farming-roja-reddy-nanda-kishore-in-india%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%223%20College%20Friends%20Take%20Uttarakhand%E2%80%99s%20Traditional%20%E2%80%98Pahadi%E2%80%99%20Salt%20To%20The%20World%2C%20Earn%20Rs%201.5%20Cr%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAfter%20all%20the%20hard%20work%2C%20Uttarakhand-based%20Sandeep%20Pandey%20was%20delighted%20that%20his%20eatery%20would%20finally%20be%20inaugurated%20soon.%20But%20fate%20had%20other%20plans.%20%E2%80%9CUnfortunately%2C%20my%20eatery%20was%20ravaged%20by%20floods%20in%20the%202013%20natural%20disaster.%20The%20road%20was%20blocked%20for%20six%20months.%20Everything%20was%20reduced%20to%20ruins%20and%20my%20restaurant%20was%20shut%20a%20week%20before%20the%20opening%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20recalls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESandeep%20was%20devastated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202009%2C%20he%20had%20quit%20his%20engineering%20career%20in%20Delhi%20to%20move%20back%20to%20his%20quaint%20hometown%20of%20Nainital%20and%20run%20a%20restaurant.%20Now%2C%20he%20was%20left%20without%20any%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThree%20months%20after%20the%20floods%2C%20as%20he%20was%20passing%20through%20a%20field%2C%20he%20noticed%20a%20few%20women%20labourers%20eating%20%3Cem%3Eroti%20%3C%2Fem%3E(flatbread)%20with%20onions%20and%20%3Cem%3Episyun%20loon%20%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F187720%2Futtarakhand-flavoured-salt-pisi-loon-traditional-food-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Epahadi%20%3C%2Fem%3Esalt%20%3C%2Fa%3Ehand%20grounded%20on%20%3Cem%3Esilbatta%3C%2Fem%3E%20(traditional%20grinding%20stone).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20offered%20me%20the%20%3Cem%3Echapati%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20salt%20made%20with%20garlic%20and%20green%20chillies.%20It%20was%20extremely%20tasty.%20I%20also%20ate%20%3Cem%3Ekakdi%20%3C%2Fem%3E(Armenian%20cucumber)%20with%20this%20salt.%20Then%2C%20I%20realised%20it%20is%20this%20salt%20that%20makes%20%3Cem%3Epahadi%20%3C%2Fem%3Efood%20so%20flavoursome.%20I%20recalled%20how%20my%20mother%20would%20pack%20this%20salt%20whenever%20I%20went%20out%20of%20town%20for%20work%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says%2C%20adding%20that%20he%20realised%20no%20one%20had%20thought%20of%20commercialising%20this%20salt%20so%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20relishing%20the%20meal%2C%20Sandeep%20also%20got%20a%20glimpse%20into%20the%20harsh%20lives%20of%20hill%20women.%20%E2%80%9CThese%20women%20were%20working%20under%20the%20MGNREGA%20scheme%20as%20labourers%20and%20their%20job%20was%20to%20dig%20ground%20and%20lift%20boulders%20%E2%80%94%20all%20for%20a%20daily%20wage%20of%20Rs%20270.%20The%20work%20was%20said%20to%20guarantee%20100%20days%20of%20employment%20in%20a%20year%20but%20the%20system%20was%20corrupt%20at%20the%20village%20level.%20There%20was%20no%20surety%20on%20timely%20payments%20and%20number%20of%20working%20days%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20cl